how to run sbatch file:

1) login to rc computing like normal
- ssh (your email)
- password
- cd /scratch/alpine/your_identikey
2) if you want to receive an email when it starts / ends the job change the code for "job.sh" at the last #SBATCH command to your email instead of mine
3) if you are ready to run file, type "sbatch job.sh" into the terminal
4) it should give you like a job number if it started
- " Submitted batch job 26308341 "
5) to quick check status type: squeue -j <jobID> (insert whatever actual job id # is, don't include the < and > signs either)
6) to show the actual output of the script with time and # of iterations and compute time type "tail -f pyjob.<jobID>.out"
7) to cancel job type "scancel <jobID>"

Right now the job.sh file is setup to run the NewUpdated.py script wiht the NACAPoints.dat file as well, but you could easily change that at the bottom of the job.sh file

